<h1>About</h1>
<p>
  This app uses <strong>OpenFlights</strong> datasets (CSV): <em>airports</em>, <em>airlines</em>, and <em>routes</em>.
  Data is imported via <code>db/seeds.rb</code> into a normalized schema.
</p>

<h3>Datasets</h3>
<ul>
  <li><strong>airports.csv</strong> — name, city, country, IATA, ICAO, latitude, longitude</li>
  <li><strong>airlines.csv</strong> — name, IATA/ICAO, country, active</li>
  <li><strong>routes.csv</strong> — airline, source airport, destination airport, stops</li>
</ul>

<h3>Relationships</h3>
<p>
  <strong>Airline</strong> has many <strong>Routes</strong>. Each <strong>Route</strong> links a
  <strong>source Airport</strong> to a <strong>destination Airport</strong>. This creates a many-to-many
  between Airlines and Airports, and a self-referential many-to-many among Airports.
</p>

<p>Pages include collection lists, show pages with associated data, search & filters, pagination, and an interactive map on airport pages.</p>

